name: Latex Diffusion V1 (reupload)
description:
New model: Abyss+Bondage+Latex (safetensor)
Abyssorangemix2 + Bondage V10 (on 0.15)
Result + Latex (on 0.3)
(needs the "vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned" to correct the greyish color)

So, after training my latex model, I was disappointed that it was so unstable and I thought it was a failure.
But then I merged it with Berrymix and I was amazed by the results. It was as if merging it had fixed all problems with it.
Then I also made some merging experiments and made the ArtEros+Berrymix+Latex model which I am using most of the time.
In both cases I had merged the raw latex model at the end 50/50 with the other model. So if you want to make your own, this might be a good starting point.

The training data was rather limited with 42 images (but a new version with a bigger dataset might be coming...).
This resulted in:
- basically 3 base outfits
- a standard latex catsuit
- a standard latex catsuit with a corset on top of it
- only latex corset with latex stockings on straps connected with the corset and long sleeved gloves; breasts are exposed
- breasts are usually big and round (due to training data)
- once merged, the resulting models have a heavy bias towards shiny outfits and slim waists (even without corset), even without any of the trigger words
